        <div style="position:absolute;bottom:20px;left:20px;right:20px;">
          <p style="color:#fff;font-size:0.9rem;font-weight:800;margin:0 0 4px;">Why It's Important</p>
          <p style="color:#B2F5EA;font-size:0.75rem;margin:0;">Employment · Immigration · Education · Residency</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p style="color:#2D3748;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:0.12em;text-transform:uppercase;font-size:0.75rem;margin-bottom:8px;">Core Reasons</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:900;color:#1A202C;margin:0 0 18px;">Why Is It Important to Get a PCC in Kuwait?</h2>
        <p style="color:#4B5563;font-size:1.05rem;line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:20px;">
          Obtaining a Police Clearance Certificate in Kuwait is crucial for several reasons.
        </p>
        <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:16px;">
          {[
            { icon: "💼", title: "Employment", desc: "Many employers in Kuwait require a PCC as part of their background check process when considering hiring an individual. It allows employers to verify the integrity and trustworthiness of potential employees, ensuring a safe working environment." },
            { icon: "✈️", title: "Immigration & Residency", desc: "Immigration authorities often request a PCC when applying for a work visa, residency permit, or citizenship in Kuwait. It confirms that the applicant has no criminal record and is eligible to reside in the country." },
            { icon: "🎓", title: "Education", desc: "Educational institutions may require a PCC from students during the admission process to maintain a secure environment for all students." },
          ].map(item => (
            <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #eef0f6;border-radius:14px;padding:20px;display:flex;gap:16px;align-items:flex-start;transition:all 0.25s;">
              <div style="font-size:1.5rem;flex-shrink:0;">{item.icon}</div>
              <div>
                <h3 style="font-size:1.05rem;font-weight:800;color:#1A202C;margin:0 0 5px;">{item.title}</h3>
